==English==

===Pronunciation===
*AHD: blo͞oz
*IPA: /bluːz/
*SAMPA: /<tt>blu:z</tt>/
*'''Rhymes:''' [[Rhmes:English:-uːz|-uːz]]

===Noun===
{{en-noun|blues|blues}}

#Plural of ''[[blue]]''.
#{{cattag|Colloquial}} A feeling of [[sadness]] or [[depression]]. Generally used with ''the''.
#: ''My trainwreck of a love-life gives me the blues.''
# {{cattag|Colloquial}} One's particular life experience, particularly including the hardships one has faced.
#: ''Your blues is just like mine.''
#: ''Your blues are just like mine.''
#A musical form, African-American in origin, generally featuring an eight-bar or twelve-bar structure and using the [[blues scale]].  Often used with ''the''.
#: ''Many great blues musicians came from the Mississippi Delta region.''
#: ''A large portion of modern popular music is influenced by the blues.''
# (''music, always singular'') {{cat|Music}} A musical composition following blues forms.
#: ''My next number is a blues in G.''

====Usage Note====
Despite its plural form, ''blues'' may be grammatically singular or plural, except where noted.

